  <p>
    An 88 percent matric pass rate dominates headlines and political speeches. Yet celebration without
    interrogation risks mistaking pressure for progress.
  </p>
  <div class="image-placeholder">Insert national pass rate headline or DBE infographic</div>
</section>

<section id="quintiles">
  <h2>When Volume Masquerades as Equality</h2>
  <p>
    Quintile 1 to 3 schools produce more Bachelor passes than Quintile 4 and 5 schools. This reflects
    volume and limited alternatives, not the collapse of inequality.
  </p>
  <div class="image-placeholder">Insert quintile enrolment vs Bachelor pass graph</div>
  <div class="evidence">
    Suggested sources:
